From Mark Waschkowski Subject Re File Manager problem In a previous article Michael R Whitchurch says Whenever I start File Manager the status bar is not displayed even though it is selected in the options If I deselect it then select it again the bar Anyone have any ideas why this is happening No not It may be that your has gotten corrupted for some unknown Have you tried re creating it by either filemanager with the save setting option on when the status bar is visible or clicking on the Control menu the one with minimize and maximize in in when everything looks proper If you have and it still doesn't work you may want to delete your and try one of these two saving procedures again to totally recreate the file from Good luck Mark Waschkowski